  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nChoose a topic you care about — like music, soccer, fashion, games, school, or anything that interests you. You're going to create a small program using everything you've learned so far.\r\n\r\n1. Pick a topic that you're excited about.\r\n\r\n2. Create **three variables**, one for each data type:\r\n\r\n   * `int` (number)\r\n   \r\n   * `string` (text)\r\n   \r\n   * `bool` (true/false)\r\n\r\n3. Use at least **one operation** to **create a new value** and **store it in a variable**.\r\n\r\n4. Write **print statements** to show what your program remembers or does.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nStart small, then build! Test your code a little at a time — you can always add more once it's working.",
